Package date

Class Date

java.lang.Object
date.Date
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Date>
public class Date extends Object implements Comparable<Date>
This class defines a date using a year, month, and day. In this class, it can check whether the date is a valid date, compare dates to one another, check if a date is in the future, and use dates to check a member's age.
Author:
Hasnain Ali, Carolette Saguil

    • compareTo

      public int compareTo(Date date)
      Compares two dates together and is able to determine whether date to be compared is after, same, or before this date.
      Specified by:
      compareTo in interface Comparable<Date>
      Parameters:
      date - Date to be compared.
      Returns:
      -1 if the date to be compared is after, 0 if the dates are the same, 1 if the date to be compared is before. This is because if the current instance is after compared to date, then this - date would return a negative number because this is after, so it's forward in time, thus yielding a negative value. The same logic applies if this is before date.

    • checkIfDobIsFuture

      public boolean checkIfDobIsFuture()
      Checks if date is after today, or not. Meant specifically for date of birth given by client.
      Returns:
      true if date is in the past, false if date is in the future or is today

    • checkMemberAge

      public boolean checkMemberAge()
      Check if member is 18 years or older.
      Returns:
      true if member is 18 years or older, false otherwise.

    • isValid

      public boolean isValid()
      Checks if date given by client is a valid calendar date. Checks if year given and month given is in valid range. Checks if day is in valid range depending on the month. If month is February, checks if it is a leap year or not, then checks if the day is valid depending on the year.
      Returns:
      true if the date is valid calendar date, false otherwise.
